    'from' => 'Joseph  Lockett jlockett@io.com',
    'body' => 'Quoth FKiesche3@aol.com:
> sector-spanning adventures that take
> you to several locales, while searching for clues to a greater mystery (since
> we are coming out of the Long Night, maybe locating old technology, mapping
> old colonies/bases, etc. could be the "push" here). Plenty of room for lots
> of red herrings here!

Those would be fun.  There\'s a _lot_ of adventure possible in (re)contacting old
colonies: I\'ve just been reading Stableford\'s *Daedalus* series (*The Florians*,
*Critical Threshold*, *Wildeblood\'s Empire*, *The City of the Sun*, *Balance
of Power* and, soon, *The Paradox of the Sets*) and all (so far) would make
excellent Traveller adventures of exploration, diplomacy, and discovery.

Or you could, for example, discover a set of old worked-out mines, dating from
after the Ziru Sirkaa.  Well, those resources aren\'t available _here_, then,
but they must have been taken elsewhere.  Who dug the mines?  Where did they
go?  Are they still technological and spacefaring, or have they fallen back
to barbarism?

Are there still Vilani holdouts with ancient legends about the arrogant invaders
from beyond the stars (Solomani from the Rule of Man)?  Would they welcome fresh
contact?

We never hear about whether the Sylean Federation just happened to be the only
other viable interstellar government expanding at the same time... could there
have been another state in conflict with them, now ousted out of the history
books after their eventual utter destruction?

> Another adventure I\'d like to see would be of a more limited scope. A
> commercial-oriented adventure, where Traders are involved in setting up a
> merchant company....  Give lots of details on finance, stock markets and the
> like--how the arrival of a rival ahead of you ruins the worth of your cargo.

Way back when Marc Miller was soliciting ideas for the new Traveller product
line, I mentioned that a series of Adventure books, on different themes for
adventures/campaigns (how-to, new rules and gear, plot hooks and a few actual
adventures) might be good for bringing in new players and expanding the horizons
of older ones.  I think I included Exploration Adventures (scouts and recontact),
Military Adventures (characters as still-active-duty), Commercial Adventures
(what you\'ve described above), perhaps others.  I\'ll have to dig out my notes....

As for the future of the published universe... is the vague "Survey" map for
Milieu 0 (in which information becomes sketchier further and further from Sylea)
going to remain the basis for the whole historical line?  Or are we going to
find more areas detailed as new Milieus arrive -- Reavers\' Deep for the Aslan
Border Wars, the Spinward Marches (obviously) for the Frontier Wars, Solomani
Rim for the Interstellar Wars, Vland for the Ziru Sirkaa, Ilelish for the
Suerrat Revolt, Antares for the Julian War, etc. etc. etc.?  If so, I fear
we\'ll encounter D&D-like trouble wherein individual referees feel cramped
when new products detail their already-developed campaign settings.

