with user level maintenance... Combat Rifleman type skills will
cover stripping and cleaning and oiling and fixing the 2 or 3
most common failures which can be field repaired, etc.  Grav vehicle
will teach you how to change the starter battery and fuses and
such... Ground Vehicle would cover the battery, fuses, oil, and
changing tires at least, things like that.  If it is normal for
average people who use something to be able to repair it to a
certain level, then that repair skill should be subsumed into
the user skill.

More specific maintenance skills should be specialist-oriented;
an armorer has armory skills in serious and depot level weapons
repair, mechanical skills in doing heavy car repair, changing out
major components, etc.


