    'body' => '>But there is another, less obvious, reminder of the Ancients. At some time in
>their travels, the Ancients visited Earth and carried away several thousand
>near-intelligent cavemen. 

If this happened c 300,000BC then the "near-intelligent cavemen" cannot have
been Homo sapiens, but some earlier human type. The small gene-pool of
abducted "cavemen" have therefore undergone 300,000 years of divergent
evolution from the base population on Terra.  The Terran population evolved
into Homo Sapiens, but the transported populations would not have done so -
they would have evolved into other geni(?) of Homo or into entirely new
species: some of these transported populations may never have evolved full
intelligence.  This means that neither the Vilani or the Zhodani can
possibly be Homo Sapiens and must belong to some other human genus.

