Actually, ironically enough, it ruins it for the player involved more 
than the GM.  

I don\'t even think that most people would try to do this intentionally.  
But lets face it, if you\'re flipping the pages of Traveller: The New Era, 
you\'re going to run into sidebars.  In fact, if for some reason you 
flipped through to the wrong set of pages, you\'d run into the pages 
detailing the campaign background.  This could be done quite 
accidentally.  At least if the stuff is in a seperate book, you have 
to get the proper book, and start leafing through.  Prevents it from 
happening accidentally.  And if you label it "For Referees Only", or 
some such, it even tells the player to beware.

I\'ve never run across a cheater in an RPG.  There isn\'t much point 
to it.  If I did, it would be the last time they ever gamed with me as 
a Referee, or as a fellow player.

But yes, it would hurt the player more than the referee.

