>On  8 Jun 96 at 14:34, Nick Munn spewed:

>It occurs to me that most aspects of a religion could actually be
>covered by a sociology skill, which actually might be a whole lot 
>more broad-based as a skill...

Religion isn\'t a skill, but Theology is a knowledge.

I had a player back in the late 70\'s that wanted to play a Navy
Chaplin in a game.  We cribbed up a character sheet for him with
anthropology, sociology, phycology, philosophy, and recruiting
included.  I gave him a Theology skill too, but I don\'t recall exactly
