    'body' => 'On Sun, 9 Jun 1996, Tom Miller wrote:

> Actually, that gives me an idea.  Here, are using CT tech levels, my opinion
> of our current levels.
> 
[dilineation of tech level equivalents for various fields clipped for 
brevity]
> Avergae Technological Level for Earth:  7
> 
> Any comments on this?

Sure!  :)  I consider the Traveller tech levels to be a set of numerical 
representations of levels at which various technologies are achieved /on 
average/.  I ignore the earth-year equivalents given in the last column 
on the chart, and just consider the various tech levels to be 
independent of eachothr.  That is, Earth happens to have advanced in 
computer technology faster than the "average" world which has achieved 
tech level 8.  

Each culture is going to have its own mix of technologies, depending on 
where their emphasis lies.  The United States has had, for a number of 
decades, an emphasis on military technology, for instance.  A less 
warlike culture might be at tech level 8 for medical technology 
purposes, for instance, while remaining at tech level 5 in military 
weapons.  

Sure, the CT tech level chart needs some minor fixes, but it\'s not as bad 
as it might, at first, appear.  

- -Joe
