    'topic' => 'Religion - a skill? -Reply',
    'body' => '>I think the question of religion skill raises an important point: do  skills
>define a character\'s origin, or does the character define what and  why
>the skills are? In other words, does a character become `religious\'  or
>knowledgeable about religion (a) because she has that skill or (b) 
>because that is a background which explains (some of) the skills that 
>character has?

I think it\'s up to you to come up with your own character\'s history, and
either case could apply. The character could have a religion skill because
he or she is highly interested in the topic or is a religious person, or he or
she could have the skill because the character\'s parents forced the
character to go to a religious school for the first 18 years of the
character\'s life.

In either case, the religion skill would be warranted, and could be of use
in several situations (like being on a world with a Theocratic government,
perhaps). 

