suited to zero-g than hydroponics. Better suited for shipboard too, due
to the reduced mass. 

>  ::>Medicine (DM) (DH) [I like the idea of Med-1 being 1st Aid up to Med-4
>  ::>being surgeon].
> 
>  No, not a default.  Only a minority ever learn even First Aid
>  beyond "I got an owie.  Lemme put an adhesive bandage on it".

I agree with Marc Miller\'s decision to *seperate* "first Aid" (up thru
EMT) and Medicine. I\'ve had fairly extensive first aid training, and I
know some folks with EMT, Nursing and medical training. Medical and
"first aid" *do* belong seperate. The skills are *not* the same. In
fact, many doctors who aren\'t trained in emergency medicine aren\'t any
better than First Aid 1! Likewise, an EMT\'s training is very
specialized. 

I *would* say that Medical skill can be *used* as First Aid 1. And
*maybe* First Aid can be used as Medical 1. And Medical skill should
include "Nursing" (start with it in fact)

As for First Aid being a default, remember, this is for *characters*.
They *should* get a "no penalty" (but no bonus either) to try to do
first aid.


