>You\'d think just about all data except the fact that there is a star 
>in such and such an area would be lost after 1700 years.  I doubt 
>that Sylea & surrounds would have data of any kind other than 
>positions, and class of stars for worlds in for example the Vland sector.  
>I\'ve always viewed the rise of Sylea as kind of an intergalactic 
>Renaissance coming out of the Dark Ages.  If this is a valid model 
>(maybe it\'s not), then its doubtful Sylea is going to know much of 
>anything about a lot of worlds...even obsolete information, and the 
>pocket empires on the fringes are going to know even less.
