> happened to GDW? TSR sued them? For what?

An old story.  It all started when Gary Gygax, designer of AD&D, 
either left T$R, or got fired by them, or whatever it was.  Anyways, 
GDW, looking to get into the Fantasy RPG market, hired him.  Gygax 
wound up designing Dangerous Journeys for them, which was not all 
that successful for GDW.  To make matters worse, T$R claimed that 
Gygax had been working on and designing DJ when Gygax was still 
working for them.  GDW contended that he did not.  TSR wound up suing 
GDW for a pretty large sum of damages, and won.  It put GDW in a 
fiscal crunch from which they never really recovered.  Ironic, 
because Dangerous Journeys itself was not a successful product for 
them, or so I\'ve heard.

