    'date' => '16 Jun 1996 18:54:43 GMT',
    'body' => '>I suppose it would be too much to hope that someone out there has produced a
>deckplan-building tool, have they?

Depends on what you mean.

I have a set of standard items created in SuperPaint.  When I\'m detailing a
room, I just copy-&-paste them in.

Admitedly they look a bit low-tech, because I started doing this in colour
for Space 1889, and haven\'t put a lot of time into conversion.

Now, if a kind artistic soul was to email me some 300 dpi PICT (or GIF or
TIFF) top-view images of beds, fresher cubicles, control consoles... I could
quickly convert all my deckplans to gloriously coloured masterpieces :-)

Seriously, though, I\'d be willing to do a lot of the drawing is someone could
create nice fittings.  My current standard is 2 yards/metres to the inch with
no squares draw on the plan.  Instead, I place a small red cross (0.25 in) at
the centre of the square.  This is less obtrusive, and also means that narrow
corridors don\'t look strange.

I think Matt has some of my 1889 deck plans at the heliograph site.  Check
them out for an idea of what I\'m talking about.
