    'body' => 'This talk about there being no alternative FTL is mistaken, I think.  While
other FTLs aren\'t mentioned in CT products, I know that in the TNE Rulebook
on page 331 it says 

\'Projected technology is divided into several different fields.  Each field
represents a solution to a problem or goal.  In the case of the stardrive
field, a universe\'s projected technologyy can be jump drive, stutterwarp,
natural warp points, star gates, hyperspace or psionic shifting...\'

Also, on page 332, a small table showing different areas of technology shows
this

\'Representive Field                     Effects 
 Stardrive                              SEVERAL styles of approach (jump drive
                                        star gates, etc.)\'

Well, I suppose that shows that in ALL traveller there are different styles
of stardrives, but the TNE book also goes on to say that only ONE should be
allowed in each universe (kind of dumb if you ask me).

Peter Miller

