The problem here is TL.  Book2 doesn\'t ever state TL.  We might assume
that it\'s TL11 due to the jump2 drive, but nothing else in the design
matches HG, so why should the TL?

In Traders and Gunboats the Far Trader is listed at TL10, but it has J2.
Book2 is broken (I say this because I\'m sure more ships were designed
with HG than B2, so HG wins :-).

I would also add that the technology that makes a sub-TL12 ship no
longer exists since MM decided on the Fusion+ hook.  I\'d be interested
to see if a HG design at TL12+ matches with a QSDS design.

As someone else noted, the economics have always been broken.  Muir did
some interesting number-crunching on this (since it\'s right up his alley
).

