    'body' => 'On 06/18/96 at 01:15 AM,  anwfh@orion.alaska.edu (William F. Hostman)
said:

>>> According to the CT and MT histories (and I do not see why
    this wou have changed in the New Era, but I haven\'t really
    used much of that material), the six "Major Races" eac
    discovered the same type of Jump Drive technology
    independently.  This is the only ftl travel available to t >>>
"physics" of the game as it is written.

If you want to introduce alternate FTL tech you can, but Jump is the
\'canon\' approach.  

I\'ve used stutterwarp, hyperdrive, and ST-like warp drive in the past,
but I\'ve always limited FTL to just one way per game.  I could see
independent development of 2 or 3 methods, but I don\'t know if that
situation would continue long.  Wouldn\'t the best way soon become the
way everyone used?

The lack of FTL communications is also an important factor in
Traveller fictons. I *like* keeping communications down to the speed
of the ships.  I did run one game where there were FTL commo and
sensors, but limited their use by giving them a very short range and
high energy requirements.  They ended up being used in-system only.

>There is one other alternative, albeit above TL17; grandfather has
>constructed gates that allow instant travel to a pocket dimension,
>where you drive a day or so to another gate out, and have wound up
>between 2 and 8 parsecs distant.

I remember that, too!  It\'s been a *long* time since I looked at
Secrets of the Ancients. ;->

Eris
