:This is true, unfortunately lets face it the average stutterwarp ship
:could run rings about a HEPLAR ship, not to sure about grav plates but
:introducing something like this totally changes the face of space.  You
:can do it just be very careful about the type of travel you wish to
:offer.

   Stutterwarp would tromp all over any drive that requires acceleration.
It doesn\'t accellerate, it just moves. So it can change direction
instantaneously and literally stop on a dime.

   As an aside, it would be fun to run a beer & pretzels game that had
both Jump and Stutterwarp. The way I\'d do it would be to give Jump and SW
similar performance, but make SW *extremely* expensive so that only
governments could possibly afford them. You would rapidly see an
interesting dichotomy - military vessels would all get SW, while civilian
and commercial vessels would make-do with cheap Jump Drives. Civilian combat
with military vessels would be a joke. Pirates would have a hard time,
unless they managed to get their hands on a bootleg, possibly defective
SW drive. In which case, they would be *real* dangerous - until the drive
broke down. <g>

   The way I see it, this means SW drives will probably be strictly
controlled (no reason for civies to have one) and probably booby-trapped
to prevent missappropriation by "non-superpowers" that don\'t have SW, or
pirates.


