what s/f is _about_.

   Players are *always* going to find ways to ruin the referees day.
It\'s much better to just keep the game simple and assume that Things
Happen and have a rational system set up to deal with the potential
problem. Trying to drop a PB? Have a patrol cruiser *just happen* to be
in the Right Place at the Right Time. If you\'ve already got the players
used to the idea of an patrol presence, they shouldn\'t object to it.

   Such a game is *much* more fun than a game where the referee says
"hmm, I don\'t like that - sorry you can\'t do it"

   What *is* the difference betwen dropping a rock at 50km/sec and
dropping a rock at .1c? In either case, they are guilty of war crimes
and would be chased to the ends of the universe, in my game.

   Players should be discouraged from doing things like this, but there\'s
better ways than "you can\'t do it".


