Well, first of all, the immediate thing that you probably wouldn\'t know
about the Aslan sans Alien module is the gender division.

Aslan females outnumber Aslan males about 3 to 1.

The females take on a variety of non-combat roles - including all
medical, financial, technical, technical support, educational,
etc, etc, issues.

Aslan males deal almost excusively with leadership, politics and
warfare. According to the skill slisted, Aslan males are
unable to deal with even simple concepts like _money_ without
having a special skill to do so.

The Aslan will often ignore a non-Aslan\'s true gender and refer
to a being using a gender selected on the basis of that being\'s
job or skill set. E.g. a ship\'s captain will always be refered
to with male pronouns, a ship\'s doctor or engineer will always have
female pronouns used for them. This faux pas is probably more common
among males than females, as females get educated at least.

This is very unlike the Klingons, who are all ass-kicking
types apparently. Also, Klingons seem to have a more 
"human" sex ratio - men do everything, with the occassional
female character so the producers can throw a pair of breasts
onscreen. (ST and all its offspring still have the most awful
females roles.)

