Andrew,

In a way, you are right that the rules are, in many ways, part and parcel 
of the Imperial setting.  For example, the oft-cited price fixing for 
cargo and passage rates.  

But, here\'s another look at the issue:

The Traveller set I first purchased was the Deluxe Starter Edition (two 
8-1/2 by 11" booklets, with Adventure 0, Introduction to Traveller, and 
the Spinward Marches map.  We hadn\'t used prepared adventures since the 
D&D days, so I didn\'t actually read Adventure 0 until about 10 years 
later (!).  I don\'t recall reading Intro to.., either.  So, we set about 
playing Traveller using only the core rules.  I made up planets as I went 
along.  There was no "Imperium."  
Then I bought Supplement 3, The Spinward Marches and that gave me data on 
the planets on my map.  But there still wasn\'t an Imperium.
It wasn\'t until a few years later that I had enough Supplements to piece 
together an idea of what the Imperium was like.  Gradually, our campaign 
environment came to resemble the official Traveller universe.

Now, did our play suffer from not using the Imperium?  No, it didn\'t.  As 
a matter of fact, we had other sci-fi games (notably Star Frontiers), and 
we preferred Traveller to Star Frontiers /even though we didn\'t know 
about the official Traveller setting/!  The rules, the clarity, the 
professionalism...these things made Traveller the superior product it was 
for us.

Now, obviously Marc Miller is going in the direction of giving Traveller 
distinct characteristics outside of the rules (ie, the discussion of 
symbols of the Imperium to be used to clearly indicate a given drawing is 
of a Traveller setting).  So, I think the official Traveller setting will 
be even stronger than before.  I think this is a good idea.

But I still hope the rules will be separate from the setting - even if 
only separated into sections of the same book.  That way, people will at 
least have the clear choice of making their own setting.

This is all moot now, though...we\'ll just have to see what the game looks 
like in a month! 


- -Joe
