    'ts-index' => '1996-07-05.ae377',
    'body' => 'Thanks for the tip, I\'ll see if I can find it at Half-price Bookstore.

If you can get ahold of it, try Cachalot by Alan Dean Foster (my favorite 
author)  You\'ve got humans, whales, neat alternate technology (Gel Suit), and 
something dark and mysterious in the deep, et al.  I can\'t seem to remember if 
Dolphins play a role in the story, probably do.

Although Foster is not one to let realism get in the way of a good story, I 
think it is a must-read if you\'re designing a water world.  And Alan Dean 
Foster is the kewlist of the kewl.

