to contact one of the Aslan starfaring clans.  The meaning of the
name "Aslan" is lost in obscurity as far as Imperial citizens are
concerned.  :)  

There are other examples of such things in old Bestiary articles.  
For instance, there\'s an animal called a "bloodvark" that looks
like a cross between a bloodhound, aardvark, and canister vaccuum
cleaner, and is trained to find fugitives on many worlds.  On some
of them it is called a "hoover", but nobody knows why....  (Hoover
being a well-known vaccuum cleaner brand in the US.)  This was in
one of the old JTAS issues.  There\'s probably other examples, too.

The idea seems to have been to have subtle, plausible jokes for the
20th century players that the 57th century characters wouldn\'t get.
(Both the Hoover Vaccuum Cleaner Co. and Narnia books could easily 
survive into the Terran Confederation era, for instance.)

