I intend to track down a machine readable listing of the level 3
braille standard one of these days. I suspect that it will be a close
to optimal text encoding system.... :-)

>>Check out what the call "chording" keyboards.
>   Why stop there? One player wanted his "hand computer" configured
> so that you "typed" using intricate spell-weaving type gestures :-).

Ah, you have a budding technomage. :-)

>>Given the above, there\'s no need to bother displaying a keyboard.
>>Select "text input" and then just flex your fingers in the right
>>patterns. You don\'t even have to flex them all that much, just enough
