I suspect that we\'ll reach the situation described in an Analog story.
Everyone will have their personal AI, and it\'ll download the local laws
as you enter the jurisdiction. Then it\'ll advise you on what you need
to worry about.

Lawyers and laws haven\'t gotten a lot of attention from computer
science types yet. But it turns out that the notation used for computer
langauge syntax diagrams works *very* well for laws. And the result is
both more compact and easier to understand. 

Lexical analysis is going to make things *very* different. It\'s a
relatively new tool, and hasn\'t (yet) been applied in this area. 

As for plot ideas, how about a "practical joke" by a "friend". He loads
a program into your "glasses" that does to your vision and hearing what
things like "jive" and "valspeak" do to text.

