    'index' => 'ae429',
    'month' => '07',
    'body' => 'I\'ve always assumed that "The Long Night" was more a political than a
technological phenomena.  Various sources such as MTJ #4 (the material on
Gateway) have indicated that there was quite a bit of interstellar travel
during "The Long Night".  I would imagine that there were many TL 10-11
and even a few TL 12 world with a goodly number of ships.  Heck the
Darrians prospered during the long night.  However, there was no central
government.  

I would imagine that the largest single pocket empire would coven no more
than (at most) 2 or 3 subsectors.  To the Imperial government this
represents chaos, too folks of a more libertarian perspective the Long
Night might well be known as the era of freedom. 

As I see it Year 0 is very different form the stone-age horror of the
RC/TNE era.  There would be many small florishing pockets of interstellar
society, expeditions to far reaches of space...  However, the Syleans
would be the only people who managed to combine TL 12 with a sector-wide
government.  With these resources at their command it would be relatively
easy for them to expand and incorporate surrounding worlds and
confederations.  Given that many of these worlds and confederation would
join willingly, the Imperium could grow quite readily.   Once the 
Imperium covered several sectors none of these minor confederations could 
possibly stand in its way.  

Comments?  Disagreements?


- -John R. Snead jsnead@netcom.com


