    'body' => ' I never really thought of the Imperium as very similar to 20th Century
America. Considering the distances and lack of instant communication (FTL
Radio) I think it\'s diversity would be similar to the period western
expansion from 1850-1900 A.D.. 
 Example: Many Germans settled in the area of Milwaukee, with them they
brought their language, culture and politics. They had a common language of
English with Americans outside of Milwaukee, but in Milwaukee, among their
own community, they still spoke German. The only reason German culture has
been reduced in influence is it\'s direct exposure to American Culture (The
Mix) for an extended and continuous period of time. 
 Now imagine if Milwaukee was a planet on the fringe of the Imperium. Changes
in the Imperium; Styles, entertainment, and Ganglic slang would take a year
at minimum to work it\'s way out to the Isolated planet of Milwaukee. 
 The Isolation then becomes more then distance, it becomes cultural.
Milwaukee ends up building it\'s culture that is based on their German orgins,
other planets nearby, a slight Imperial Influence and on what they need to
develop in the face of changes on the local level (Events and Environment).
This being true for 11,000 seperate systems, I would think that only a
handful universal cultural characteristics would exist in the Imperium unlike
the nearly universal cultural characteristics in the U.S..
 

Keith
