Am I losing e-mail again, or has nobody compared this to Nowhere Man
yet? Somehow I ended up watching most of the last season finale, even
though I\'d only seen 1-1/2 other episodes.

For those that don\'t know the story, the premise of Nowhere Man is
that the government has erased this man\'s identity and completely
covered everything up. He remembers things from the past, but there
is no evidence that it ever happened. In the last season finale,
they explained everything and it was completely different from what
you were being led to believe. The star apparently was a government
agent in an agency that had the capability of completely replacing
people (faces, memories, and all). He had built this personality
and history for himself and it was never real.

There are many ways this could go. Did he do it to test the limits
of the technology, as has been suggested? Was he forced into it?
Did he intend all along to subvert the agency, but this was the
only way they\'d let him out? All three? Does he have an entirely
different personality from before he became/was made into a spy?
Is he really the president of the universe, only in hiding?


