    'body' => 'Rick,

I refereed a few Traveller PBEMs. You can find some info
on one of the games in http://astro.sns.it/~mstiavel/Traveller/tpbm.html

My experience was:
- -it is useful to prepare a rather detailed description of the 
scenario/campaign (2-3 pages), so that players who sign in will not drop
off after a couple of turn because things are different from what they 
expected.
- -it is dangerous to have more than one turn per week (too much work for the
referee, this is the reason why we stopped the game)
- -it is useful to have pregenerated characters that the players can select
- -it is necessary to enforce strict turns (start/end etc) otherwise
players go off on different timelines

This is just my experience and need not to be representative..of my
players only two had a lot of Traveller experience.

         Cheers,
              Massimo

P.S. depending on when you start ( I am very busy in the next couple of 
weeks) and how often you plan to play I may be interested in joining
you PBEM.
