    'index' => 'ae548',
    'body' => 'The past few posts have discussed the \'splintering\' of the various Traveller
players.  I realize they exist, but people have to realize that it will
always be there.  Take D&D for example, how many people played it as written
and with no embelishments?  The same is true with Traveller.

For those who care (and those who don\'t), here is how I play Traveller:

1.  "Basic" character classes (MT)
2.  Character generation (TNE)
3.  Task resolution (MT)
4.  Vehicle/ship construction (MT)
5.  World generation (as published on the \'net by Jeff Zeitlan and others)
6.  Time Period (CT)
7.  Various other tidbits taken from a variety of sources (Traveller
Chronicle,     Challenge, etc)

So basically it is MT with a twist.  

Like many others, I will still buy T4.  However, it will probably not be
played in its true form.  I\'ll pick it apart and keep what I like and
discard the rest.
Thanks,

