    'topic' => '  The Imperial Establishing Document',
    'body' => 'Marc writes:

>Assuming this document is less than 1,000 words, what would it say?
>What other provisions would it have. What would be the loopholes?
>What is its name?

   One possible source of inspiration would be the British Magna Carta,
which spells out the rights of nobles.  The Imperial version of this
document would certainly do that as well.  Additionally it would spell
out the rights of commoners--here the U.S. or Canadian constitutions
would be of assistance.

   You can count on there being something that states something along
the lines that the word of the Emperor is law, something akin to Papal
infallibility.  Ideally it would also address the issue of Imperial 
succession, and the Moot\'s role in it (you\'ll also want a loophole allowing
for the possibility for succession through assassination as well with an
eye toward the Barracks Emperors and the Rebellion yet to come).

   It probably would not address a detailed government structure, as that
probably isn\'t an issue in the early years (everything centers on the
Emperor in any event).

   All I can think of at the moment.  More later if I come up with anything.

Regards,

Harold


   

   

